<HEADLINE> WEU Chief Urges Flexibility in Crisis Management </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, March 17 (Xinhua) -- The Western European Union (WEU)
chief Jose Cutileiro Tuesday urged flexibility in decision making
within the politico-military institution to better handle crises.
</P>
<P>
The consensus principle, which the WEU had to apply in the
decision-making procedure regarding sending troops to a theater of
operations, should be flexible enough to give priority to WEU
operations over coalitions of the willing, Cutileiro told a
gathering in Brussels.
</P>
<P>
The gathering was held to mark the 50th anniversary of the
signing of the Brussels Treaty which serves as the founding
document for the WEU as well as the North Atlantic Treaty
Organization.
</P>
<P>
Crisis management is a main mission of the institution which
was founded in 1955 and now has 10 full members. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
