<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EC, CFO Fail to Reach Deal on World Cup Ticket Sales </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, March 17 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission(EC) and
the French organizing committee(CFO) for the 1998 Soccer World Cup
failed to reach a deal on selling the remaining tickets for the
finals outside France.
</P>
<P>
European Competition Commissioner Karel Van Miert Tuesday met
with CFO managing director Jacques Lambert, but failed to make a
deal, a spokesman for the EC said.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said the meeting had been "constructive" and that
the EU executive expected a final proposal within this week.
</P>
<P>
Van Miert said last week that he wanted the CFO to make more
than 160,000 unsold tickets available for soccer fans outside
France.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said the Commission, the European Union(EU)'s
executive body, may take legal measures which could result in a
fine for breach of EU fair competition rules.
</P>
<P>
Soccer fans in other EU countries complain about the
concentration of ticket sales in France, which they believe
discriminate against other citizens in the EU.
</P>
<P>
The World Cup finals are scheduled for June 10 to July 12.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
