<HEADLINE> Tire Giant's Profits Surge </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, March 17 (Xinhua) -- German tire manufacturer Continental
said in Hanover Tuesday that its profits increased by two thirds
to 322 million marks (177 million U.S. dollars) last year,
compared with 192 million marks (106 million dollars) in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The result was achieved through increased sales, which rose by
7.2 percent to 11.2 billion marks (6.2 billion dollars), according
to the Hanover-based company.
</P>
<P>
Continental also included the changes in its type range and
restructuring efforts as factors contributing to the surge in its
profits. 
</P>
</TEXT>
