<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at GMT 14:30, March 17 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Seven Iranian university students, including a world
mathematics Olympic gold medalist, were killed and several others
injured when the bus carrying then turned over Monday night in
Iran's southwestern province of Khuzestan.
</P>
<P>
Tehran radio reported Tuesday that the accident occurred on the
highway between Ahvaz and Kharramabad when the students were on
the way back from a mathematics competition held in Ahvaz.
(Iran-Road)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BANGKOK -- The Export-Import Bank of Japan and 14 other
leading Japanese banks have signed a contract to provide 600
million U.S. dollars to help Thailand's cash-strapped exporters.
</P>
<P>
The loan, to be guaranteed by the Thai Finance Ministry,
carries a term of five years with a three-year grace period, the
Bangkok Post said Tuesday.(Thailand-Japan-Loans)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ANKARA -- Turkey has proposed an outline for stopping the
continuing turbulence in Kosovo, Muslim region of Yugoslavia,
warning that the disorder may expand into a major international
crisis over all the Balkans unless a compromise is reached.
</P>
<P>
State Minister Ahat Andican said that leaders of the Federal
Republic of Yugoslavia and representatives of the Kosovo people
should immediately launch a comprehensive dialog aimed at finding
a way to facilitate the solution process.(Turkey-Kosovo)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- U.S. President Bill Clinton met with Sinn Fein
leader Gerry Adams Monday night, hoping to push the Northern
Ireland peace process forward.
</P>
<P>
After a 15-minute talk with Clinton, Adams and the Sinn Fein
chief negotiator Martin McGuinness said their talk had focused on
positive discussions and praised the president for his commitment
to search for peace in the province.(Clinton-Adams)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BEIJING -- The ongoing First Session of the Ninth National
People's Congress (NPC), China's top legislature, this morning
held its fifth plenary meeting, at which Zhu Rongji was approved,
by way of voting, as premier of the State Council, the cabinet.
</P>
<P>
The meeting also approved by voting Zhang Wannian and Chi
Haotian to be vice-chairmen of the Central Military Commission
(CMC), and Fu Quanyou, Yu Yongbo, Wang Ke and Wang Ruilin members
of the CMC.(China-NPC-New Premier)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
VIENNA -- The price of a basket of seven crudes plunged to
11.83 U.S. dollars a barrel last week, the lowest in nearly a
decade, the Organization of Petroleum Exporting Countries (OPEC)
said on Monday.
</P>
<P>
It had planned to hold a special meeting of its Market
Monitoring Committee on Monday to consider ways of stopping the
price decline.
</P>
<P>
However, members, including Saudi Arabia and Venezuela, refused
to attend, forcing OPEC to put off the meeting until the end of
March.(OPEC-Oil Price) 
</P>
