<HEADLINE> Yeltsin's Illness Postpones CIS Summit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin,
who has caught cold and is receiving treatment, suggested that the
Commonwealth of Independent States (CIS) postpone their impending
meeting until April.
</P>
<P>
Doctors on Tuesday recommended that Yeltsin continue treatment
in a countryside residence and advised him to spend some of the
day in bed, Itar-Tass news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin is now being treated with antibiotics, medications to
improve breathing functions and stop his cough, a spokesman for
the Kremlin press service reported.
</P>
<P>
The Russian president caught a cold Last Friday and is
suffering from a throat infection. He is now looking well and his
condition is improving, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The CIS summit was scheduled in Moscow for March 19.
</P>
<P>
The CIS was founded in December 1991, and it groups 12 member
states of the former Soviet Union that disintegrated in 1991. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
