<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> More Zimbabwean Women Have HIV: W. Bank </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, March 17 (Xinhua) -- About 40 percent of the
Zimbabwean women who visit Ante-Natal clinics in the capital here
are infected with the HIV virus which causes AIDS, says a World
Bank report.
</P>
<P>
The Zimbabwe News Agency Ziana Tuesday quoted the report which
has just been released in Bulawayo, the country's second largest
city as saying Zimbabwe has one of the highest rates of HIV
infection in the world.
</P>
<P>
It says the gains Zimbabwe has been making in lengthening life
expectancy are being eroded.
</P>
<P>
"Between 1950 and 1990," according to the report, "life
expectancy had increased from 40 to 63 years, but has since been
brought back to 40 by AIDS."
</P>
<P>
Zimbabwe's National AIDS Control Program Director Evaristo
Marowa has said more than 700 people are dying of AIDS every
week, while 1.5 million are living with the HIV virus, and
300,000 have full blown AIDS.
</P>
<P>
The World Bank report says that by the year 2020 HIV/AIDS will
be the single largest infectious killer of adults in their prime
in the developing world.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1997, says the report, 30 million adults, of
whom 90 percent of them in developing countries, had contracted
the virus. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
