<HEADLINE> UK Inflation Rises Slightly to 2.6 Pct in February </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Britain's annual rate of
underlying inflation, which excludes home loan payments, rose
slightly to 2.6 percent in February, against forecasts of 2.5
percent, according to figures released Tuesday by the Office for
National Statistics (ONS).
</P>
<P>
This meant that the government missed its target inflation rate
of 2.5 percent last month after hitting it in January for just one
month since the general election.
</P>
<P>
The ONS said that the headline rate of inflation rose to 3.4
percent from 3.3 percent in January.
</P>
<P>
The figures re-opened the debate about whether another interest
rate rise will be necessary to check inflation.
</P>
<P>
The rise was mainly due to the fact that prices in the
clothing, footwear and household goods sectors rebounded last
month after the January sales. 
</P>
</TEXT>
