<DOCNO> XIE19980318.0012 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU, France Hold Talks Over Credit Lyonnais Bank </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, March 17 (Xinhua) -- France may soon present a plan
on the rescue of its Credit Lyonnais Bank, a European Union (EU)
spokesman said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
European Competition Commissioner Karel Van Miert and French
Finance Minister Dominique Strauss-Kahnhas held "constructive"
talks Monday in Brussels on the future of the troubled
state-controlled bank, said the spokesman for Van Miert.
</P>
<P>
The bank, which fell to the verge of bankruptcy at the
beginning of the 1990s, is being rescued for the third time.
</P>
<P>
The long-term profitability of Credit Lyonnais, which is
expected to report a profit when it announces its annual results
Thursday, depends partly on the softening of the terms of a
restructuring plan imposed by the European Commission in 1995 in
return for clearing a huge government bailout.
</P>
<P>
The European competition commissioner, who has met with the
French finance minister regularly since the beginning of 1998,
wants France to privatize the bank and to sell all its retail
banking network outside France.
</P>
<P>
Van Miert has reopened an investigation into all subsidies
received by Credit Lyonnais since it nearly collapsed in the early
1990s. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
