<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UK Ex-Minister Aitken Released on Bail </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Britain's former cabinet minister
Jonathan Aitken was released Tuesday on bail after being
questioned over allegations of perjury and conspiracy to pervert
the course of justice.
</P>
<P>
He was arrested earlier in the day after he offered himself for
police questioning. His 17-year-old daughter, Victoria, was
arrested Monday over allegations of conspiracy to pervert the
course of justice.
</P>
<P>
Aitken, 55, said he had "voluntarily attended" a police
interview in London over allegations made against him and his
daughter by the Guardian newspaper.
</P>
<P>
The former chief secretary to the Treasury took the Guardian
newspaper and Granada Television to Britain's High Court last year
over allegations they made in 1995 about his links with Saudi
Arabian business associates over an arms deal.
</P>
<P>
They had accused Aitken of procuring prostitutes for Arab
businessmen, of trying to arrange arms sales to Iraq before the
Gulf War and of allowing a Saudi associate to pay for a stay at
the luxurious Ritz Hotel in Paris.
</P>
<P>
Aitken, a rich businessman, had links with many powerful people
in the Arab world which he used to help win lucrative defense
contracts for Britain. 
</P>
</TEXT>
