<HEADLINE> Singapore's Exports to Nigeria Up by 31% </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Singapore's exports to Nigeria
increased by 31.7 percent to 201.4 million U.S. Dollars in 1997,
the News Agency of Nigeria reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
This compared to 144.2 million Dollars in the previous year,
the official agency quoted Loi Eng Koon, leader of the
Singaporean Trade Development Board as saying.
</P>
<P>
According to her, Singapore's main export items of video and
sound recorders, television and radio sets and parts for office
and data processing machines, all increased in the past year.
</P>
<P>
The board was targeting the west African region next as part
of its efforts to pioneer Singapore's entry into the emerging
market, she said.
</P>
<P>
Eight Singapore companies from various sectors accompanied the
board on the business mission which has taken them to Cote
d'Ivoire, Ghana and Nigeria. 
</P>
