<HEADLINE> Nigeria Grows More Maize than Cassava: Statistics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria boasts as the world's
number one producer of yam and cassava, the Federal Office of
Statistics (FOS) said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
An FOS publication entitled "National Agricultural Sample
Census 1993/94" says that however, it produces more maize than
the two crops, yam and cassava, with 54 percent of all holdings
in the country cultivating it.
</P>
<P>
The document says that Imo State in the south records in
highest figure of maize production with 93 percent, followed by
Edo and Anambra states, which grow 90 and 89 percent
respectively.
</P>
<P>
Yam and cassava, traditional food for many Nigerians, are
grown more in the northern part of the country than in the south.
</P>
</TEXT>
