<HEADLINE> Russia Ousts Two Norwegian Diplomats </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, March 17 (Xinhua) -- The Russian Foreign Ministry
announced a decision Tuesday to expel two Norwegian diplomats from
Russia, the Interfax news service reported.
</P>
<P>
The two Norwegians -- Rune Castberg, a councillor of the
Norwegian embassy in Moscow, and Ole Bjornoy, consul of the
Norwegian general consulate in Murmansk -- were ordered to leave
Russia by March 20.
</P>
<P>
The reason for the expulsion is that "Russian competent
authorities have incontrovertible evidence of involvement in
activities incompatible with their official status," the Foreign
Ministry's release said.
</P>
<P>
Last Friday, Norway expelled two Russian diplomats and declared
three former employees of Russian foreign missions persona non
grate on suspicion of espionage.
</P>
<P>
In the wake of the scandal, the Norwegian prime minister
postponed his visit to Russia, scheduled for this week, that
caused a negative reaction in Moscow.
</P>
<P>
Spokesman for the Russian Foreign Ministry Valery Nesterushkin
said that the expulsion of Russian diplomats from Oslo was "an
episode in our bilateral relations which does not encourage their
constructive development."
</P>
<P>
"Activity of the Norwegian special services toward Russia and
its citizens does not contribute to normal development of
cooperation between our countries," the ministry said. 
</P>
