<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Afonso Dhlakama, Chairman of the
majo opposition party, the Mozambican National Resistance Party
(Renamo), reiterated here Tuesday that his party demanded to join
the Technical Secretariat of the Election Administration ( STAE).
</P>
<P>
At a press conference, Dhlakama said that Renamo is demanding
its involvement in the STAE so as to check the irregularities in
last year's voter registration.
</P>
<P>
He said that "we hope to have complete right in the STAE,"
adding that the irregularities like the missing of the
registration book was "planned".
</P>
<P>
Another reason for Renamo's demand to join the STAE, he said,
is that the STAE will function also for the general elections for
1999.
</P>
<P>
The current STAE serves as a tool for the ruling Mozambican
Liberation Front (Frelimo) in its malpractice, he said.
</P>
<P>
Dhlakama said that his party has no ill intention to ruin the
local elections designed to be held on June 30.
</P>
<P>
The reason for Renamo to join the STAE is to correct all the
irregularities and win back people's trust to it, the opposition
party leader said.  
