<P>
TEHRAN -- A traffic accident killed 18 university students and
three university staff members in Iran's southwestern province of
Khuzestan Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
A truck run into the bus carrying girl students from Mashhad
Shahed Medical University, Iran's northeastern province of
Khorasan, who were returning from a visit to Ahvaz, Khuzestan's
capital city. (Iran-Road Accident)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
NICOSIA -- The U.N. chief's top envoy for Cyprus arrived here
early Wednesday for a six-day visit in a bid to bring the leaders
of the Greek and Turkish Cypriot communities back to the
negotiating table.
</P>
<P>
Speaking upon his arrival, U.N. Secretary-General's Special
Advisor for Cyprus, Diego Cordovez said the U.N. is seriously
concerned about the situation in Cyprus.(Cyprus-U.N. Envoy)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
SEOUL -- Foreign financial institutions are expected to enter
South Korea in the second half of this year to buy local banks, a
South Korean organization said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Samsung Economic Research Institute in a report listed
Seoul Bank and Korea First Bank as the top targets, which are
under preparation for sale, as are other small ailing
banks.(S.Korea-Foreign Capital)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
