SINGAPORE -- Vietnam called on developed countries to provide
more assistance to countries in the Southeast Asian region to
enable these countries out of the current financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
"We call on developed countries to provide more their
responsible assistance so that the countries in the region can
soon get out of the crisis," visiting Vietnamese President Tran
Duc Luong said here Wednesday. (Singapore-Vietnam-Assistance)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ISLAMABAD -- Pakistani Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif Wednesday
stressed the need for creating an environment of peace and
stability in South Asia for economic development and regional
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
"We firmly believe that peace and security are key to the
economic development of the region," Sharif said while
inaugurating the Second Economic Cooperation Conference of the
South Asian Association for Regional Cooperation (SAARC) here
Wednesday morning.(Pakistan-SAARC-Sharif)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
SEOUL -- South Korea Wednesday urged Japan to apologize for
atrocities committed in World War II against comfort women, or sex
slaves, and to shoulder responsibility for them.
</P>
<P>
"The Korean people will respect the Japanese if Japan
acknowledges the atrocities committed against comfort women,"
Foreign Affairs and Trade Minister Park Chung-soo said here in an
interview with Japanese media.
</P>
<P>
The comfort women were those who were forced to sexually serve
Japanese soldiers during World War II.(SKorea-Comfort Women)
