<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hunters, Rockets to Vie for League Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Liaoning Hunters and Chinese Army
Rockets beat their respective semi-final rivals on Wednesday to
set up a showdown for the title of the Chinese Basketball Division
A League.
</P>
<P>
The Hunters, who upset Shandong Flaming Bulls 70-63 in the
first leg, prevailed 70-62 on the road in the second of the
best-of-three semi-finals.
</P>
<P>
The Flaming Bulls, who finished second in the regular season,
appeared too nervous to breach the well-knit defence of the
visitors, trailing 29-41 in the first half.
</P>
<P>
The hosts, cheered by a sell-out crowd of 5,000, stepped up the
attacks after the break and managed to close the gap to one point.
</P>
<P>
But the Hunters, runners-up of last season, snapped the fierce
rally in time on two three pointers by point guard Li Xiaoyong,
who finally ended up with a game-high 28 points.
</P>
<P>
In Chongqing, defending champions Rockets fought back from a
first half 34-44 behind to rout the visiting Beijing Ducks
82-57.
</P>
<P>
The Rockets and Hunters will launch their best-of-five final on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
In Hangzhou, Zhejiang Squirrels trounced Shenyang Army 86-50 in
the fourth round of the play-offs, which drew the last four
finishers in the regular season and on a double round-robin
format.
</P>
<P>
In Beijing, the Airforce Eagles overpowered Sichuan Pandas
82-57.
</P>
<P>
The Squirrels and the Eagles, both maintained unbeaten
in the last four rounds, have kept their Division A berth while
the winnless Shenyang Army and the Pandas were relegated. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
