<HEADLINE> Jiang Delivers Speech on Military Science (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 18 (Xinhua) -- China's military science research
should develop more rapidly to meet the demands of an
ever-changing situation, Chinese President Jiang Zemin, who is
also general secretary of the Central Committee of the Communist
Party of China (CPC), said here today.
</P>
<P>
Jiang's remarks came while attending the celebration of the 40th
anniversary of the founding of the Military Academy of Sciences.
</P>
<P>
China's national defense and army modernization drive have
entered into a crucial cross-century stage, he said, emphasizing
that military research should adhere to the guidance of Mao Zedong
and Deng Xiaoping's military thoughts, adapting to the development
of world military trends, and making a greater contribution to the
country's military modernization drive, said Jiang, who also is
chairman of the Central Military Commission of China.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that over the last four decades researchers of the
academy have compiled a large number of military works, translated
and published foreign military works, and provided the Central
Military Commission with many valuable research reports and
consultations which have played an important role in pushing the
cause of China's national defense and helping build the army.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said the principles of people's army and people's war in
Mao Zedong's and Deng Xiaoping's military thoughts will have
long-term guiding significance for the army. Military science
research will deviate from the correct course without the guidance
of the principles, he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
