<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Launches Pilot Scheme for Fixed Rate Mortgages </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 18 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Mortgage
Corporation (HKMC) signed an agreement with two commercial banks
Wednesday to launch a pilot scheme for promoting fixed rate
mortgages.
</P>
<P>
Under the six-month scheme, the two participating banks, Chase
Manhattan Bank and Dao Heng Bank, will offer home buyers mortgage
loans at a fixed rate of 10.5 percent for the first three years.
The HKMC agreed to purchase from each of the two banks eligible
fixed rate mortgages up to 250 million HK dollars (32 million U.S.
dollars).
</P>
<P>
At Wednesday's signing ceremony, Financial Secretary Donald
Tsang, who chaired the board of the HKMC, said: "Today is a very
big day for us in mortgage financing in Hong Kong. Fixed rate
mortgage products will bring significant benefits to Hong Kong."
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong home buyers now have an additional choice of mortgage
arrangement which can protect them from adverse movements in
interest rates, said the official. The participating banks will
also add a source of steady fee income from providing fixed rate
mortgages.
</P>
<P>
If the pilot scheme is successful, the HKMC may appoint more
participating banks and increase the amount available for fixed
rate loans, sources from the HKMC said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
