<DOCNO> XIE19980318.0079 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> News Analysis: Quality of Cadres, A  Decisive Factor (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 18 (Xinhua) -- The ongoing First Session of the
Ninth National People's Congress (NPC), China's legislature, has
completed the process of examining and deliberating on a number of
work reports submitted by the State Council and departments under
it and shifted its emphasis onto the choice of new government
leaders.
</P>
<P>
By now, people are fully aware of the importance of having
competent cadres -- an issue underlined time and again by top
leaders of the Communist Party of China (CPC).
</P>
<P>
This is not because new problems have occurred among the ranks
of cadres but because a new situation in the country requires more
competent cadres.
</P>
<P>
Mao Zedong, the late CPC chairman and founder of New China, had
a well-known saying: once policies and strategies have been
determined, cadres are the decisive factor. Many deputies to the
NPC share the view that Mao's idea in this regard is still of
great significance for the China of today.
</P>
<P>
China's cross-century development program has taken clear shape
during the period from the convening of the 15th CPC National
Congress to the current NPC session. Specific measure have also
been worked out to resolve problems that have cropped up in the
course of reform and development.
</P>
<P>
Up to now, leaders of central government departments for a new
term of office have been chosen following the formation of a
collective leadership of the CPC Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
At a time when policies have been formulated and the lineup of
leaders determined, to raise the quality of cadres becomes a
pressing task.
</P>
<P>
Whether the principles and policies of the Party and government
can be implemented smoothly and how fast development in all fields
can be hinge on the role of cadres at all levels.
</P>
<P>
At the present stage, it can be said with certainty that the
overall quality of cadres at all levels falls short of what their
country requires in its march toward the next century with
ambitious economic development goals to accomplish.
</P>
<P>
This is an issue raised by Jiang Zemin, general secretary of
the CPC Central Committee, years ago and listed on the agenda of
the 14th CPC Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
It is obvious that an increasing number of people will pay
close attention to this issue in a changing situation.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980318.0080 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> News Analysis: Quality of Cadres, A Decisive Factor (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Many NPC deputies hold the view that qualified cadres should
first of all grasp Marxism-Leninism, especially Deng Xiaoping
Theory. This is because Deng Xiaoping Theory has served as the
guiding principle for China's two-decade-long reforms and opening
up to the outside world. It is also because the country's
prevailing policies are all based on this theory.
</P>
<P>
In the last couple of years, leaders at the top level have
stressed the importance of having a correct political orientation
and urged cadres to keep the country's overall interests in mind.
It is a basic requirement for cadres at all levels to follow
unswervingly the Party Central Committee with Jiang Zemin at the
core.
</P>
<P>
This is understandable since, if cadres at all levels fail to
take the overall interests of the nation into consideration or
lack a firm political faith, or do not match their deeds with what
they say, it would be difficult to push ahead with reforms and
continued implementation of the open policy in China, a vast
country with a huge population, at a critical period for its
development.
</P>
<P>
Without doubt, cadres should also have knowledge, especially
that in the fields of science and technology, and market
economics. Otherwise, they would find it difficult to deal with
complex situations and new problems.
</P>
<P>
Another issue of top concern among NPC deputies is cadres' work
style and state of mind. Cadres at all levels should maintain the
Party's fine tradition of "serving the people wholeheartedly" and
never depart themselves from the masses. Moreover, they are not
allowed to abuse their power to seek personal gains.
</P>
<P>
Deputies also urge cadres at all levels to work in a pioneering
spirit because China is now taking a road that has not been
traveled before within and outside China.
</P>
<P>
It can be predicted that the training of competent cadres is
abound to be placed once again on the agenda of the Party and
government after the conclusion of the Ninth NPC First Session.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
