<HEADLINE> Shanghai-Paris Air Link to Resume on May 12 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Air France announced here today
that on May 12 it will resume its flight from Paris to Shanghai,
the French airline's second destination in China.
</P>
<P>
Air France will have two flights a week until September, when
it will add a third. Its Paris-Beijing flight will also be
increased from the current four flights to five a week in
September.
</P>
<P>
Air France, whose aircraft flew between Shanghai and Paris
during 1966-1973, obtained management rights on January 16 to
resume the flight in accordance with a memorandum of understanding
between the two countries' aviation authorities.
</P>
<P>
The French company's Asia-Pacific regional general manager,
Marie-Joseph Male, said that China together with the rest of Asia
has been a booming market for his company in recent years.
</P>
<P>
Last year, Air France transported more than 34 million
passengers, an increase of 10 percent over the previous year. The
number of passengers from China increased by 15 percent.
</P>
<P>
Male said that a substantial number of passengers that fly to
Paris from Beijing are residents of Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
China Eastern Airlines Co., Ltd. also announced today that it
would open its Shanghai-Paris flight on July 7, with two flights a
week until September, when it will add a third flight.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
