<HEADLINE> China Reports Steady Economy in January, February </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 18 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese State Statistics Bureau
reports steady economic growth in the first two months of 1998.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, the added value of all State-run
enterprises and non-State companies each with five million yuan in
sales reached 274.3 billion yuan during the two-month period, up 8
percent compared with the same period last year. The growth rate
was 2.4 percentage points less than the 1997 level.
</P>
<P>
The slower economic growth is attributed to a longer Spring
Festival holiday, market controls, and output restrictions.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show the fixed assets investment of State-owned
companies at 65.4 billion yuan, an increase of 10.2 percent from
the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
Retail sales in the period amounted to 485.6 billion yuan, up
9.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, imports and exports in the first two
months were worth 42.5 billion U.S. dollars, a year-on-year
increase of 8.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
Imports amounted to 24.8 billion U.S. dollars, up 15.7 percent,
and exports, 17.7 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Prices continued to fall during the period, and the retail
price index fell 1.7 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
