<HEADLINE> Macao Paper Applauds China's New Leadership </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, March 18 (Xinhua) -- The third generation of China's
leadership is time-tested as politically mature, capable, and
trustworthy, a leading Macao newspaper said in a commentary on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Macao Daily News said the new leadership elected at the
on-going session of the 9th National People's Congress (NPC)
enjoys a high prestige among the Chinese people as they have scored
outstanding achievements in their official careers, and won the
heart of the people.
</P>
<P>
The NPC session in Beijing has elected Jiang Zemin China's
president, Li Peng chairman of the Standing Committee of the 9th
NPC, and Zhu Rongji premier of the State Council.
</P>
<P>
"Time has proven that the third generation leadership with
Jiang Zemin at the core is politically mature, capable, and
trustworthy to the Chinese people," the newspaper said. "Its
members' renewal or transfer to their new positions will guarantee
the continuity of national policy and the effective operation of
the government."
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, some Macao members of the National Committee of the
Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC) and
chiefs of local communities also spoke highly of the new
leadership.
</P>
<P>
Ma Man Kei, who was re-elected vice-chairman of the CPPCC
National Committee, said on Tuesday night after returning from
Beijing that the new leadership "commands popular support", and
"accords with the aspirations of the people."
</P>
<P>
"The minute-long applause at the session (when the new
leadership was elected) indicates they enjoy a high prestige and
are trusted by the Chinese people," Ma said. "I am very delighted
and have composed a poem for the new leadership."
</P>
<P>
Some other CPPCC members and chiefs of local communities said
the new leadership will "lead China into the 21st century
successfully."
</P>
<P>
Over the past two weeks, all Macao newspapers have given
prominence to the NPC and CPPCC sessions in Beijing.  
</P>
</TEXT>
