<HEADLINE> Hanoi Calls For More Assistance From Developed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam called on developed
countries on Wednesday to provide more assistance to countries in
the Southeast Asian region so as to enable these countries to get
rid of the current financial crisis soon.
</P>
<P>
"We call on developed countries, international financial and
monetary institutions to provide more their responsible assistance
so that the countries in the region can soon get out of the
crisis," visiting Vietnamese President Tran Duc Luong said at the
state banquet given in his honor by Singapore President Ong Teng
Cheong.
</P>
<P>
The Vietnamese leader said that the finance and currency crisis
had "very negative effects on many countries in the region,"
which, he stressed, required efforts for surmounting this
difficult challenge.
</P>
<P>
"We share with the affected countries the difficulties and
challenges and at the same time try to follow closely the
situation in order to draw necessary experiences," Tran Duc Luong
said.
</P>
<P>
The Vietnamese President, who arrived here Wednesday afternoon
on a three-day state visit, also said that Vietnam will continue
to "consistently pursue the foreign policy of independence,
sovereignty, openness, multilateralization and diversification,
actively integrating itself into the region and the world."
</P>
<P>
"The priority is given to the development of relationship with
regional and neighboring countries," he stressed.
</P>
<P>
The Vietnamese President's current state visit is the first
ever by a Vietnamese Head of State to Singapore.
</P>
<P>
Singapore Foreign Ministry said that during the historic visit,
President Luong will meet with Singapore President Ong Teng
Cheong, Prime Minister Goh Chok Tong, and Senior Minister Lee Kuan
Yew.
</P>
<P>
He will also attend briefings by the National University of
Singapore, Land Transport Authority, and the National Computer
Board, the Ministry said.
</P>
<P>
In his speech, President Ong Teng Cheong said that Vietnam has
made big strides in its efforts to integrate itself with the
international community and has proven itself to be a constructive
and an active member of the ASEAN (Association of South East Asian
Nations).
</P>
<P>
Singapore welcomes Vietnam's efforts to play a more active role
in other important regional fora, like the ASEAN Regional Forum
(ARF) and the Asia-Europe Meeting, the President said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
