<HEADLINE> Beijing Holds 3rd International Space Technology Exhibition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 18 (Xinhua) -- The 3rd International Space
Technology and Applications Exhibition opened today in Beijing's
China World Trade Center.
</P>
<P>
Over the next five days, companies from the United States,
France, Germany, Russia, Britain, and other countries will
demonstrate the latest aerospace technology for launch vehicles,
satellites, propulsion systems, data and image processing,
geographical information systems, and global positioning systems.
</P>
<P>
The sponsors of the event, the China Great Wall Industry Corp.,
say that the developments of space technology are being applied
more and more to agriculture, forestry, marine science,
irrigation, environmental protection, transportation, and
meteorology, affecting people's daily lives.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese area will show the latest developments in space
technology for remote sensing, with a special section on popular
space technology and applications designed for the public.
</P>
<P>
China Aerospace Corp. will hold an international conference on
"The Development of International Space Technology and
Applications for the 21st Century".
</P>
<P>
The event is held every two years in Beijing and is becoming a
significant forum for international space technology and
applications and exchanges. The first one, in 1994, attracted more
than 30 organizations from 7 countries, and the second one in 1996
attracted 105 organizations from 14 countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
