<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Investment, Trade Center Established in Cote d'Ivoire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, March 18 (Xinhua) -- The China Hualong Investment,
Development and Trade Center opened in Abidjan in Cote d'Ivoire
recently as one of the six Chinese trade centers in Africa.
</P>
<P>
The trade centers are the result of Vice-Premier Li Lanqing's
visit to six West African nations in 1995.
</P>
<P>
The Cote d'Ivoire center was built by a construction company
in Gansu Province and is operated by the Chinese Foreign Trade and
Economic Cooperation Ministry.
</P>
<P>
The 1,043-sq-m exhibition center in downtown Abidjan has room
for 15 to 20 enterprises to display their goods.
</P>
<P>
Since last July, it has brought 21 Chinese delegations to Cote
d'Ivoire. It hosted an exhibition in December of machinery,
electronics, textiles, and health products of 15 Chinese
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1997, 66 Chinese enterprises had shown an
interest in doing business with the center.  
</P>
</TEXT>
