<HEADLINE> HK Papers Hail China's New Premier Zhu Rongji </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong newspapers Wednesday
warmly welcomed Zhu Rongji becoming China's new premier.
</P>
<P>
Commentaries, photos or profiles about Premier Zhu were
published in almost all local newspapers which agreed that the
election of Zhu as China's new premier is an embodiment of
people's aspirations.
</P>
<P>
Zhu was elected China's new premier by deputies to the Ninth
National People's Congress (NPC) in Beijing Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Sing Tao Daily said in an editorial that the newly elected
Premier Zhu is well versed in economy, enjoying high prestige both
at home and abroad.
</P>
<P>
China is now concentrating its energies on developing its
economy and opening up, so it needs a premier like Zhu, it said.
</P>
<P>
The new Chinese leadership including President Jiang Zemin has
impressed the Hong Kong people very well and will win support
from them too, the paper said, adding that this will be a best
guarantee for Hong Kong's prosperity and stability after its
return to China.
</P>
<P>
A commentary by Ming Pao Daily News said the new Chinese
leadership with Jiang Zemin as president, Li Peng as chairman of
the NPC Standing Committee and Zhu Rongji as premier of the State
Council, has been formally formed and will lead the Chinese people
 in advancing toward the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
Their successful coordination will surely guarantee the correct
 decision making and high administrative efficiency, greatly
pushing forward the governing of China according to law, it said.
</P>
</TEXT>
