<HEADLINE> Road Accident Kills 21 in Southern Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, March 18 (Xinhua) -- A traffic accident killed 18
university students and three university staff members in Iran's
southwestern province of Khuzestan Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
A truck run into the bus carrying girl students from Mashhad
Shahed Medical University, Iran's northeastern province of
Khorasan, who were returning from a visit to Ahvaz, Khuzestan's
capital city, Tehran Radio reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The report did not give further details about the accident and
the figure of injured, but adding that the injured were rushed to
hospital for treatment.
</P>
<P>
The accident happened Tuesday after the country's seven top
mathematics students were killed in the same province when their
car overturned in a highway Monday.
</P>
<P>
The mathematics students, including a doctorate student and a
gold medalist of the world mathematics Olympiad, were returning
from a mathematics competition held in Ahvaz.
</P>
<P>
The two traffic accidents before the Iranian new year (to start
March 21) holidays shocked the Iranian authorities, and reports
said that Iranian supreme leader Ayatollah Ali Khamenei Tuesday
issued a statement, expressing regret and sorrow over the Monday
tragedy.
</P>
<P>
Iranian police have said most of the traffic accidents in the
country were caused by carelessness of drivers.
</P>
</TEXT>
