<HEADLINE> Pak Wants to Resolve Issues With India Through Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani Prime Minister Nawaz
Sharif Wednesday reiterated that his country wants to resolve all
outstanding issues with India through talks.
</P>
<P>
The Pakistani government's policy "is clear that we want to
resolve the issues with India through bilateral negotiations,"
Sharif said while talking to the media at the inauguration of the
Second Economic Cooperation Conference of the South Asian
Association for Regional Cooperation held here this morning.
</P>
