<HEADLINE> Snowy Weather to Continue in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, March 18 (Xinhua) -- The bad weather accompanied by
snow and heavy winds that began on Monday will last until the
weekend in Turkey, the semi-official Anatolia News Agency reported
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Temperatures in the country have dropped to eight to 12 degrees
centigrade from 16 degrees days ago, the agency quoted information
from the Meteorology General Directorate as saying.
</P>
<P>
Due to slippery road, a passenger bus from Turkey's capital
Ankara to Samsun along the Black Sea turned over in Merzifon town
of Amasya province, about 250 kilometers northeast of the capital,
at small hours on Wednesday, killing at least four people and
injuring 22 others, and three of them in serious conditions, the
agency said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the heavy snow, which is continuing, has been
disrupting daily life in many cities and causing traffic delays
and accidents.
</P>
<P>
Snow also blocked many village roads in the provinces of
Kayseri, Samsun, Amasya, Malatya, Bolu and Hakkari and caused
power outages and breakdowns in communication systems in these
regions.
</P>
<P>
Primary and high schools in many provinces were given two-day
holidays due to the bad weather, the agency said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
