<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin Appoints Cabinet Members </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 18 (Xinhua) -- President Jiang Zemin today
issued a presidential decree appointing vice-premiers, state
councillors and other members of the State Council, China's
cabinet.
</P>
<P>
Following is the full text of the presidential decree, Jiang's
second since assuming the presidency of a new term:
</P>
<P>
In accordance with a decision of the First Session of the Ninth
National People's Congress of the People's Republic of China, I
hereby appoint:
</P>
<P>
Li Lanqing, Qian Qichen, Wu Bangguo and Wen Jiabao as vice
premiers of the State Council;
</P>
<P>
Chi Haotian, Luo Gan, Wu Yi (female), Ismail Amat (Uygur) and
Wang Zhongyu as state councillors;
</P>
<P>
Wang Zhongyu as secretary-general of the State Council
(concurrently);
</P>
<P>
Tang Jiaxuan as minister of foreign affairs; Chi Haotian as
minister of national defense (concurrently); Zeng Peiyan as
minister in charge of State Development Planning Commission; Sheng
Huaren as minister in charge of State Economic and Trade
Commission; Chen Zhili (female) as minister of education; Zhu
Lilan (female) as minister of science and technology; Liu Jibin as
minister in charge of Commission of Science, Technology and
Industry for National Defense; Li Dezhu (Korean) as minister in
charge of State Ethnic Affairs Commission; Jia Chunwang as
minister of public security; Xu Yongyue as minister of state
security; He Yong as minister of supervision; Doje Cering
(Tibetan) as minister of civil affairs; Gao Changli as minister of
justice; Xiang Huaicheng as minister of finance; Song Defu as
minister of personnel; Zhang Zuoji as minister of labor and social
security; Zhou Yongkang as minister of land and natural resources;
Yu Zhengsheng as minister of construction; Fu Zhihuan as minister
of railways; Huang Zhendong as minister of communications; Wu
Jichuan as minister of information industry; Niu Maosheng (Manchu)
as minister of water resources; Chen Yaobang as minister of
agriculture; Shi Guangsheng as minister of foreign trade and
economic cooperation; Sun Jiazheng as minister of culture; Zhang
Wenkang as minister of health; Zhang Weiqing as minister in charge
of State Family Planning Commission; Dai Xianglong as governor of
the People's Bank of China; and Li Jinhua as auditor-general of
the National Audit Office.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Zemin
</P>
<P>
 President of the People's Republic of China
</P>
<P>
 March 18, 1998
</P>
<P>
</P>
