<HEADLINE> Romanian FM Confident over Treaty with Moldova </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Negotiations over a major
political treaty between Romania and the Republic of Moldova are
at an advanced stage, said the Romanian Foreign Minister Andrei
Plesu on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
At his first press conference since being appointed to the post
two months ago, Plesu said, "I am confident that, given the very
good atmosphere in which contacts have been proceeding, things
will run in a good direction."
</P>
<P>
But the Foreign Minister cautioned that the treaty is a very
serious thing and has to be negotiated in a careful and
responsible manner.
</P>
<P>
Plesu had said before that the treaty with Moldova, the former
Romanian territory known as Basarabia, was not to be signed in a
rush. Basarabia was taken from Romania in 1940.
</P>
<P>
"We have no aggressive intention, no plan not to respect an
independent state's self-determination, but there are affinities
between us, a communion of language, culture which cannot be
neglected or treated in haste," Plesu stressed.
</P>
<P>
So far, two meetings have been held to negotiate the terms for
the treaty, the latest being in February. The next round is
scheduled for May. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
