<HEADLINE> Romania to Sign Treaty with Russia in Fall </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Romanian Foreign Minister
Andrei Plesu said Tuesday that negotiations over a treaty with
Russia will go on and that if everything goes well, it can be
signed in fall.
</P>
<P>
He made the statement at a press conference, referring to the
basic treaty under negotiations between Romania and Russia.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that negotiations should continue over both "moral
and material reparations."
</P>
<P>
He added that Romania insists to create a joint commission to
trace the treasury Romania entrusted Russia under German
occupation during World War I. 
</P>
</TEXT>
