<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Company Increases Size of Container-Ship Fleet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 18 (Xinhua) -- China Ocean Shipping
Co. (COSCO), the largest shipper in China, now has all 13 of its
ships ordered overseas at the end of last year.
</P>
<P>
The last ship, a 3,400-TEU (twenty-foot equivalent unit)
vessel, was recently delivered from the ROK's Samsung Heavy
Industries Co. and is operating on the Mediterranean to US route.
</P>
<P>
COSCO's ship contracts were with the ROK company and a Japanese
company. Six ships have a 5,250-TEU capacity, five have a
3,400-TEU capacity and two are 836-TEU vessels. They bring the
number of COSCO's ships to 144 and its handling capacity
exceeding 210,000 TEUs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
