<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ambassador Hails Sino-Tunisian Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 18 (Xinhua) -- The Tunisian ambassador to China
today hailed the "active development" of the Tunis-China relations
and expressed the hope that the economic and cultural links
between the two countries would be further advanced.
</P>
<P>
Mohamed Mongi Lahbib, the ambassador, said that the Sino-Tunisian
relations are being strengthened on the basis of unity, mutual
trust, respect and support.
</P>
<P>
Tunisia and China share many similarities, and the ways of
bilateral cooperation in various fields could be diversified,
added the ambassador in an interview with Xinhua before the
Independence Day of Tunisia, which falls on March 20.
</P>
<P>
The ambassador cited the fertilizer factory initiated jointly
by China, Tunisia and Kuwait in north China's Qinhuangdao city as
an encouraging model of the "South-South Cooperation".
</P>
<P>
He said that China's economic achievements have "again brought
about hope" for the developing countries.
</P>
<P>
Lahbib noted that Tunisia is now enjoying a stable economic and
social situation and there are favorable investment opportunities
in the areas of textile, agriculture, food, power, electronic
industry and automobile parts.
</P>
<P>
The increasing contacts between the business people of the two
countries would help enhance the smooth growth of bilateral trade,
the ambassador said.
</P>
<P>
Chances of bilateral cooperation also exist in the fields of
personnel training, language teaching, especially in medical
treatment and the exchange of experience in agriculture. 
</P>
</TEXT>
