<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NPC Session Approves Composition of State Council </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 18 (Xinhua) -- The sixth plenary meeting of the
First Session of the Ninth National Peope's Congress (NPC) this
afternoon approved Li Lanqing, Qian Qichen, Wu Bangguo and Wen
Jiabao to be vice-premiers of the State Council.
</P>
<P>
Chi Haotian, Luo Gan, Wu Yi, Ismail Amat and Wang Zhongyu were
approved to be state councillors.
</P>
<P>
The meeting also approved the State Council's
secretary-general, ministers, president of the People's Bank of
China, and auditor-general of the National Audit Office in line
with the State Council's new structure.
</P>
<P>
At 3:00 P.M., a letter containing Premier Zhu Rongji's
nominations for State Council posts was read out at the full
session of the NPC deputies. The NPC deputies then were given
ballots bearing the names of the nominees for State Council's
vice-premiers, state councillors, secretary-general, ministers,
president of the People's Bank of China and auditor-general of the
National Audit Office.
</P>
<P>
The deputies then cast their votes, approving the
nominations.
</P>
<P>
By way of pressing on voting devices, NPC deputies also elected
the chairmen, vice-chairmen and members of eight special
committees under the Ninth NPC.
</P>
<P>
The composition of the Ninth NPC Financial and Economic
Committee had been approved earlier by the NPC session.
</P>
<P>
Tian Jiyun, an executive chairman of the session presidium,
presided over today's plenary meeting.
</P>
<P>
A total of 2,941 NPC deputies attended the meeting. 
</P>
</TEXT>
