<HEADLINE> Seminar on Dhaka City Management Reform </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, March 18 (Xinhua) -- A three-day workshop on "Dhaka City
Management Reform" ended here Tuesday with a call for
service-providers to cater to the needs of the over 9 million
residents in the capital city, press reports said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The seminar, jointly organized by the Bangladesh Rural
Advancement Committee and the Bangladesh Center for Advanced
Studies, discussed such issues as conservancy, garbage clearance,
land use, health and sanitation, rural migration, sewage, water
supply, traffic jam and emission pollution.
</P>
<P>
Representatives from Khulna, Rajshahi and Chittagong of
Bangladesh, Calcutta and Surat of India, and from the Asian
Development Bank made presentations at the seminar.  
</P>
