<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NZ Stocks Finish Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, March 18 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand sharemarket
rallied at the close on Wednesday following a record high reached
on Wall Street Tuesday night and the Reserve Bank's announcement
on easing monetary conditions.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 Index ended 26 points higher at 2,337 with a
turnover of 98 million dollars (55 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Telecom led the rises, jumping 18 cents to 869 cents. Also
higher were Air New Zealand, up 2 cents to 206 cents, Carter Holt
Harvey, climbing 7 cents to 267 cents, and Lion Nathan, gaining 9
cents to 447 cents.
</P>
<P>
Among the weaker leaders, Brierley Investment eased 1 cent to
115 cents and Fletcher Energy dropped 5 cents to 588 cents.
</P>
<P>
Overall, there were 58 rises and 37 falls.  
</P>
</TEXT>
