<HEADLINE> Two More Czechs Die in Mountaineering Accident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Two Czech climbers have died in
the snow storm when they ignored warnings to scale Mt. Karkonosze
on Saturday, a newspaper here reported on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
It said the duo, one 30 years old and the other 24, plunged 200
meters to their death when they fell from a craig in heavy snow.
</P>
<P>
The paper said the mountain authority had issued stern warning
against any climbing activities when weather forcasts predicted
snow storm on Saturday in the region.
</P>
<P>
Accidents have overshadowed the popular sport recently as eight
people were killed in four occasions in less than three weeks
since the beginning of March. 
</P>
