<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fujian Announces Elimination of Idle Development Zones </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Coastal Fujian Province has
decided to eliminate 30 idle development zones in an attempt to
increase available farm land.
</P>
<P>
The decision resulted from an investigation which revealed that
30 of 123 approved development zones have not been developed due
to irrational planning.
</P>
<P>
The zones in question cover 8,733.33 ha, with farm land
accounting for 62 percent of the total. Construction is
progressing smoothly on approximately 7,000 hectares.
</P>
<P>
The province has also decided to launch a new investment
solicitation campaign to provide funding for zones lacking
appropriate levels of development. 
</P>
</TEXT>
