companies, institutions and government departments recently
visited China for three days to join Chinese counterparts in
discussions of environmental issues.
</P>
<P>
They also sponsored a China-Northern Europe Development
Conference at Shanghai's Fudan University. The conference focused
on state-of-the-art environmental and energy technology, as well
as development prospects in Northern Europe and the world as a
whole.
</P>
<P>
A Danish company and related department plan to sponsor a
similar seminar in Benxi, a major city in northeastern China's
Liaoning Province.
</P>
<P>
In addition, a group of Danish companies will participate in
an environmental science and technology seminar in the east China
cities of Wujin and Yixing.  
