<HEADLINE> Wen Jiabao, Vice-Premier of State Council </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Following is a biographical
sketch of Wen Jiabao, whose nomination to be vice-premier was
confirmed today at the First Session of the Ninth National
People's Congress (NPC).
</P>
<P>
Born in September, 1942; native of Tianjin; joined Communist
Party of China (CPC) in April 1965.
</P>
<P>
Studied in Department of Geology and Minerals at Beijing
Institute of Geology from 1960 to 1965, took postgraduate courses
in structural geology in his Alma Mater from 1965 to 1968.
</P>
<P>
For ten years after 1968, worked with Geomechanics Survey Team
under Gansu Provincial Geological Bureau, serving successively as
technician and political instructor. Became team's deputy chief in
1978 and deputy director of Gansu Provincial Geological Bureau in
1981.
</P>
<P>
Beginning from 1982, Wen worked in Ministry of Geology and
Mineral Resources, serving successively as head of Policy and
Regulations Research Section and vice-minister.
</P>
<P>
In 1985, was appointed deputy director of General Office of CPC
Central Committee. Was director of the office from 1987 to 1992.
</P>
<P>
Alternate member of secretariat of CPC Central Committee
1987-92; alternate member of Political Bureau of CPC Central
Committee and committee's secretariat member between 1992 and
1997.
</P>
<P>
Has been member of Political Bureau and secretariat member of
CPC Central Committee since 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
