<DOCNO> XIE19980318.0169 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Luo Gan, State Councillor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Following is a biographic sketch
of Luo Gan, who was nominated as State Councillor by Premier Zhu
Rongji and approved by the Ninth National People's Congress at its
First Session today.
</P>
<P>
Luo, born 1935, native of Jinan, Shandong Province, joined the
Party 1960, graduated from Freiburg Institute of Mining and
Metallurgy in Germany, senior engineer.
</P>
<P>
Studied at the Pressure Processing Department of Beijing
Institute of Iron and Steel Engineering, 1953-54; Studied German
language at Karl Marx University in Leipzig GDR, did field work in
the Leipzig Iron and Steel Plant and Metal Casting Plant the
following year and, afterwards studied at the Freiburg Institute
of Mining and Metallurgy for six years.
</P>
<P>
Did research work in the Mechanical Engineering Research
Institute under the First Ministry of Machine-building and
served as technician and project chief, 1962-69; served as
office chief for preparing the establishment of a research
institute under the First Ministry of Machine-building in Luohe
City, Henan Province, later deputy director of the Zhengzhou
Machine-building Research Institute of the Ministry, 1970-80.
</P>
<P>
Served as deputy director of Henan Provincial Import and Export
Commission, director of the Provincial Science and Technology
Commission, 1980-81; vice-governor of Henan Province, secretary of
CPC Henan Provincial Committee, 1981-83; vice-president of the
All-China Federation of Trade Unions and member of Party's
Secretariat and deputy secretary of ACFTU Party Group, 1983-1988.
</P>
<P>
Served as minister of labor, secretary-general of the State
Council, secretary of the Party Group, secretary of the Working
Committee of the State Department under CPC Central Committee,
1988-93; state councillor, secretary-general of the State Council,
secretary of the Party Group, secretary of the Working Committee
of the State Department under CPC Central Committee, deputy
secretary of the Central Political Science and law Committee since
1993.
</P>
<P>
Served as member of the Political Bureau of CPC Central
Committee and member of the Secretariat of CPC Central Committee
since 1997.
</P>
<P>
Luo was elected alternate member of 12th CPC Central Committee,
member of 13th to 15th CPC Central Committees, and was elected
member of both the Political Bureau and the Secretariat of the
15th CPC Central Committee. 
</P>
