<HEADLINE> North China Port City to Link Up with Japan by Air </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, March 18 (Xinhua) -- A new air route was opened Monday
between Tianjin, a major port city in north China, and Nagoya in
Japan.
</P>
<P>
It is the first regular air route to link the north China
municipality with Japan, according to local officials.
</P>
<P>
Operated by the Air China Tianjin Branch, the Boeing 737 jet
will fly two return flights a week, on Mondays and Fridays, at the
beginning, and a Wednesday flight will be added in the near future.
</P>
<P>
With a distance of 1,869 kilometers between Tianjin and Nagoya,
each leg will require a flight time of two hours and forty
minutes.
</P>
<P>
Japan is the third largest trading partner with Tianjin, which
has attracted more than two billion US dollars of investment from
Japanese enterprises including transnationals like Matsushita
Electric Industrial Co. Ltd.  
</P>
