<HEADLINE> Shanghai Witnesses Active Foreign Exchange Trading </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai, China's major economic
and financial center, has witnessed increased foreign exchange
trading on the part of individuals.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Branch of the Bank of Communications handled
individual foreign exchange transactions valued at 367 million US
dollars during 1997, up a dramatic 214.7 percent on 1996.
</P>
<P>
The branch was the first commercial bank in Shanghai to
introduce private foreign exchange services, and early last year
became the first to offer telephone trading and after hours
services.
</P>
<P>
The bank introduced 24-hour foreign exchange services last
October, with the new services enabling clients to obtain real-time
information about major foreign exchange markets worldwide.
</P>
<P>
This year's plans call for the bank to adopt new measures to
expand foreign exchange services, with related efforts to include
an increase in foreign exchange denominated credit card
settlements and selling traveler's checks issued by various
clients. 
</P>
