<DOCNO> XIE19980318.0182 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hainan Relieves Burdens on Farmers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, March 18 (Xinhua) -- The 44 fee items Hainan, China's
southernmost island province, abolished in 1997 reduced the burden
on local farmers by some 12.27 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
A survey conducted in 12 counties and cities revealed burdens
on local farmers ranged between 10-30 yuan and accounted for three
percent of their net income in 1997, a figure noticeably lower
than the five percent national average.
</P>
<P>
The province relieved burdens on farmers by expanding budgetary
and final accounting systems to 98 percent of local
townships. Participating townships provided 92 percent of farmers
with detailed lists of fees and labor service items.
</P>
<P>
In addition, 74 percent of the townships introduced auditing
systems, and 81 percent of villages adopted open account financial
settlements.
</P>
<P>
Law enforcement departments conducted 28 related inspections
during the year. The inspectors rendered punishment to 14
officials charged with malpractices involving over one million
yuan, with eight officials subject to either punishment stipulated
by the Party or administrative disciplinary action. Four officials
were prosecuted accordint to law. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
