<HEADLINE> Shanghai United Telecom Maintains Good Reputation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 18 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai branch of China
United Telecommunications Co., established four years ago,
has established an excellent reputation enabling it to gain over
20 percent of the municipality's mobile telecommunications market.
</P>
<P>
In August last year, the company took the lead in China's
telecommunications sector by offering a compensation service for
subscribers to its 130 digital mobile phone network.
</P>
<P>
The company pledges that 50 percent of its lines will remain
open during peak periods, with subscribers receiving a two
percent discount on monthly telephone charges for every one
percentage point deviation below the promised availability.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai branch has fulfilled its pledge and raised its
February connection rate to 58.3 percent. 
