<HEADLINE> Dredgers Tackle Silting in Dongting Lake </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Eight dredgers manufactured in
the Netherlands will soon join efforts to tackle silting problems
in Dongting Lake, China's largest freshwater lake in the Yangtze
River Valley.
</P>
<P>
China purchased the Dutch dredgers with low-interest loans
provided by the government of the Netherlands. Three dredgers are
currently operating in the heavily silted lake.
</P>
<P>
The lake is prone to flooding due to an annual accumulation of
over 100 million cu.m. of dirt and sand, according to the Hunan
Provincial Water Resources Council.
</P>
<P>
The eight dredgers can reach depths of between 15-18 meters and
will have the capacity to remove 23 million cu.m of silt annually.
</P>
<P>
The flood season is rapidly approaching and local officials are
counting heavily on the capacity of the modern equipment to
strengthen this year's flood prevention program. 
</P>
</TEXT>
