<HEADLINE> Shanghai Introduces Individual Accounts for Securities Funds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Individuals and institutional
investors can now open accounts for purchasing securities
investment funds to be issued on March 23, according to a circular
released by the Shanghai Stock Exchange.
</P>
<P>
The circular, which was issued to notify local securities
agencies to begin registration, stipulates that related accounts
can only be established for tradable funds, state bonds and
various other specified.
</P>
<P>
Individuals currently holding stock accounts will be permitted
to purchase investment funds, but will be prohibited from opening
separate accounts to purchase same.
</P>
<P>
It also points out that identification cards can only be used
once to open accounts with local securities agencies which will be
responsible for the accuracy and security of personal account data.
</P>
<P>
The China Securities Regulatory Commission approved two Chinese
securities investment funds -- Kaiyuan and Jintai -- in March. The
funds totalling two billion yuan will be listed and traded on the
nation's stock exchange. 
</P>
