<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam to Stamp More Imports to Deter Smuggling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Vietnamese authorities will stick
import duty stamps on four additional categories of commodities
from April 1, said an official circular published here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Imported commodities to be stamped include television sets,
video cassette recorders, refrigerators, air conditioners, engines
and sanitary ware.
</P>
<P>
The measure is part of efforts to stop rampant smuggling of
foreign goods and to protect Vietnam's internal production.
</P>
<P>
The imports to be stamped will be regarded as smuggled goods if
they do not display the proper import duty stamps issued by the
Ministry of Finance.
</P>
<P>
Three categories of imported commodities, including liquors,
bicycles and electric fans, have been stamped since late last
year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
