<HEADLINE> Ukraine Denies Providing Weapons to Afghanistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Ukraine has denied allegations in
foreign newspapers that it violated U.N. resolutions by providing
weapons to Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
Ukrainian foreign ministry Viktor Nagaichuk said that his
country had never provided any weapons to the Taliban, the Islamic
fundamentalist group in Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
He said the allegation was aimed to ruin Ukraine's
international reputation and destroy its partners' trust.
</P>
<P>
The Tehran Times of Iran and the Washington Times in the United
States were among the newspapers which have been making the
allegations, he said.
</P>
<P>
Nagaichuk said that under the current export supervision
system, it was impossible for Ukraine to provide weapons to or
make agreements on military technology with countries to which
export of weapons is banned by the United Nations. 
</P>
