<HEADLINE> India Rebuffs Pakistan's Allegation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, March 18 (Xinhua) -- India rebuffed Tuesday
Pakistan's allegation of New Delhi's involvement in recent
violence including bomb blasts in the neighboring country, the
Press Trust of India (PTI) reported Tuesday night.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman of the External Affairs Ministry described
Pakistan's allegation as "malicious and false", and it is directed
at "covering its own involvement in these heinous acts".
</P>
<P>
Pakistan accused India last week of its involvement in recent
train blasts in Punjub province killing 16 people and injuring 26
others.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said in a statement that "the serious and endemic
ethnic and sectarian violence with which Pakistan itself is beset
is the consequence of the encouragement which the Pakistan state
has provided to fundamentalist and terrorist groups".
</P>
<P>
In recent explosions in Tamil Nadu of southern India, some
Indian politicians held Pakistan responsible for the blasts.
</P>
<P>
The Delhi police have arrested five militants including two
Pakistanis for their alleged involvement in bomb blasts in New
Delhi, capital of India, and north India over the past year.
</P>
