<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Brain-drain Costs Yugoslavia Heavily </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, March 17 (Xinhua) -- A high-tech brain-drain has cost
Yugoslavia three billion U.S. dollars during the international
embargo, the development minister said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
About 20,000 scientists specializing in high-technology flew
out of Yugoslavia between 1991 and 1996 when the embargo was
implemented against the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia, said Jagos
Zelenovic, Minister of Development, Science and Enviroment.
</P>
<P>
Zelenovic said training these scientists had cost the country
two billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
Because the government could only provide poor material
conditons, a few scentists are still remaining either abandoned
their research work or sought to change their careers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
