<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thailand's Opposition Kicks Off Censure Debate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Thai opposition leaders Wednesday
kicked off a censure debate designed to topple the present
government led by Prime Minister Chuan Leekpai.
</P>
<P>
The debate will focus on a no-confidence motion submitted to
parliament by the opposition on March 2.
</P>
<P>
The opposition reaffirmed its vow to give the government "a
very tough fight" that it claimed would reverse the public's
sentiment towards the government. But opposition leaders remained
tightlipped on what issue could be its knock-out punch.
</P>
<P>
"Things we plan to expose are not going to fade away after the
censure, as was the case with the previous no-confidence debate
(against the former government led by Chavalit Yongchaiyudh),"
said opposition leader Chalerm Yoobamrung.
</P>
<P>
The opposition is expected to concentrate on Finance Minister
Tarrin Nimmannahaeminda, blaming him for having created the
economic bubble by approving a flood of foreign loans and on PM's
Office Minister Abhisit Vejjajiva, criticizing him for having
changed the state investment regulations and thus compromising
Thailand's sovereignty.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Chuan Leekpai Tuesday expressed confidence in
surviving the biggest political challenge in his four months in
office.
</P>
<P>
Chuan also said he saw no need at the moment to change the
government alliance but added that he never expected to serve a
full four-year term despite speculation that he would do so if he
managed to maintain his popularity.
</P>
<P>
"I never think about staying a full term, but as I said before
I can't fix a time frame (for the government)," he said in a clear
indication that he would step down early once all political reform
mechanisms were in place.
</P>
<P>
"As of now there is no need to bring in any party (into the
coalition). We have a clear majority control in the House, even
though we can't call that an overwhelming majority," Chuan said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
