<HEADLINE> Mayors from Latin American Countries Meet in Havana </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Mayors from seven Latin American
cities gathered in Havana on Tuesday to discuss funding of the
Union of Ibero-America Capitals (UCCI).
</P>
<P>
Mayors from Central America, Mexico, the Caribbean and Spain
would also share experiences in promoting economic development.
</P>
<P>
The UCCI, consisting of representatives from 26 cities, was
founded in Madrid in 1982 with a view to tightening collaboration
and friendship among its members. The first meeting of mayors took
place in 1994. 
</P>
