<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Yunnan Province Benefits from Cooperation with Coastal Areas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Intensifying cooperation with
relatively developed coastal areas is helping Yunnan Province
promote local economic growth and restructuring.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai, China's largest industrial center, is the most
important partner. The two sides worked out economic cooperation
plans for the period of 1996-2000. They already have implemented
116 cooperative projects involving 1.63 billion yuan of
investment.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai-Kunming Electrical Machinery Plant, which cost the
two sides more than 10 million yuan, is scheduled to go into
production in the first quarter of this year. Shanghai Huayi Group
plans to cooperate with Yunnan's chemical sector on 20 key
projects involving 800 million yuan of investment.
</P>
<P>
The Kunming-Shanghai Fat Chemical Co. Ltd, which was designed
to make use of Yunnan's rich resources of castor-oil plant, will
produce 12,000 tons of castor oil annually.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai also helped the province train 200 senior managers and
more than 3,000 professionals.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong Province in south China is another major partner. By
the end of last year, the two sides had carried out 30 cooperative
projects with a total investment of 1.8 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
During the past five years, Yunnan has opened more than 2,000
cooperative projects with other provinces, autonomous regions and
municipalities, and used 4.4 billion yuan in the effort. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
