<HEADLINE> Computer Sales to Hit 20 Billion U.S. dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Sales in China's computer market
are expected to hit 165 billion yuan (about 19.88 billion
U.S.dollars)in 1998, today's China Daily reported.
</P>
<P>
The projected growth of 27 percent form the 130 billion yuan
sales recorded in 1997, is 14 percentage points lower than the
level of growth in 1997. China's computer market in 1997 surged
41.3 percent over that of 1996.
</P>
<P>
These figures were released in the 1997 Review of the China
Computer Market and Forecasts for 1998-2000, compiled by the
Center of Computer and Microelectronic Industry Development
Research(CCID) under the Ministry of Electronics.
</P>
<P>
CCID predicts that China's computer market will grow to nearly
200 billion yuan in 1999, and then to 240 billion yuan by the year
2000.
</P>
<P>
The three areas of the computer industry including hardware,
software and information services have registered rapid growth
compared to previous years.
</P>
<P>
The total volume for computer trading continued to grow rapidly
in 1997, with the total value of imports and exports reaching
13.16 billion U.S. dollars, up 33.1 percent from the previous
year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
