<HEADLINE> U.S. Beat China 4-1 in Women Soccer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LISBON, March 17 (Xinhua) -- American forward Mia Hamm scored
three times to pace the United States for a 4-1 victory over China
in the Algarve Cup in Louli, Portugal on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Hamm scored two goals in the final seconds of each half as the
Olympic champions won their second straight game in the eight-team
tournament.
</P>
<P>
The Americans, who hoped to win the Algarve Cup for the first
time in four attempts, dominated the game in the first 70 minutes
with several free kicks at the top of the penalty box.
</P>
<P>
Michelle Akers kicked her left foot in the 15th minute, and
Hamm blasted in the opener as Chinese goalie Gao Hong failed to
make the save.
</P>
<P>
Hamm added her second at the stroke of halftime by beating two
defenders from a header off Kristine Lilly who jumped up for the
long throw-in by Brandi Chastain.
</P>
<P>
Qui Haiyan scored for China in the 72nd minute, beating U.S.
goalkeeper Briana Scurry to end a string of 501 minutes in which
the Americans had not allowed a single goal.
</P>
<P>
In the last three minutes, the Americans scored twice through
Kristine Lilly before Hamm completed her hat trick to beat the
buzzer.
</P>
<P>
Hamm has increased her international goal total to 85 in 141
caps.
</P>
<P>
The Americans will play World Cup champion Norway on Thursday,
with a victory or a tie earning them a place in the championship
game. 
</P>
</TEXT>
