<HEADLINE> Northwest China Province to Exploit Water Resources </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Northwest China's Qinghai Province
began to enact a 13-year (1998-2010) plan to exploit water
resources in the province.
</P>
<P>
Qinghai Province is the origin of China's major rivers such as
the Yangtze, Yellow and Lanchang with 62.76 billion cubic meters
of water resources, ranking 16th in the country.
</P>
<P>
The theoretical reserve of water energy in Qinghai is 23.38
million kilowatts, ranking 5th in the country.
</P>
<P>
An official from the provincial water conservation bureau said
that in further exploiting water resources emphasis will be placed
on water conservation construction such as small hydro-stations
and anti-drought and flood campaign facilities.
</P>
<P>
In the next 13 years, Qinghai Province will fully exploit water
resources in the eastern part of the province, Qaidam Basin, the
Huangshui River Valley, upper reaches of the Yellow and Yangtze
rivers, inland lake areas, and areas around the Qinghai River.
</P>
<P>
Efforts will be taken to fully untilize water resources in the
province like repairing old water conservation projects, expanding
water-saving technology, and building small water-conservation
projects.
</P>
<P>
To ensure smooth execution of the plan, Qinghai will issue
regulations on management of state-owned water conservation
property, funds input, and water conservancy reform. 
</P>
</TEXT>
