<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, March 18 (Xinhua) -- North China's Hebei Province
has attracted 5,000 foreign investors with its preferential
policies and good investing environment.
</P>
<P>
Latest statistics show that the province has 5,028
foreign-funded enterprises, with an investment volume of 6.33
billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Among the 92 countries and regions investing in Hebei last
year, the top five by investment volume are Hong Kong, Singapore,
the United States, England and Canada.
</P>
<P>
Statistics also indicate that many foreign investors are
interested in the province's booming agricultural, trade and service
industries.
</P>
