<HEADLINE> Albania Tries to Prevent Arms Smuggling to Macedonia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Albania has pledged to make every
effort possible to prevent the smuggling of weapons and drugs
into neighboring Macedonia.
</P>
<P>
Many weapons were stolen and smuggled out of Albania when the
country's arsenals were looted during the riots early in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Albanian Prime Minister Fatos Nano told visiting Macedonian
Interior Minister Tomislav Cokrevski Monday that cooperation
between the armies and police forces of the two countries would
crackdown on illegal cross-border activities and prevent social
unrest.
</P>
<P>
In his talks with Cokrevski, Albanian Interior Minister Neritan
Ceka said that Albania does not want to see weapons smuggled out
of it causing instability in the region.
</P>
<P>
The two ministers also agreed to strengthen cooperation and the
exchange of information to crackdown the drug smuggling. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
