<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanxi Province, Germany Cooperate on Forestry Technology </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, March 18 (Xinhua) -- A new project on forestry
technology between north China's Shanxi Province and Germany will
be launched in the next four years.
</P>
<P>
To improve local farmers' awareness of scientifically utilizing
lands and forest, the project, with an investment of 12 million
marks, will cover 10 cities and counties in the province.
</P>
<P>
Sources said that 14 years ago China and Germany began their
cooperation in the field of improving forestry technologies in
Shanxi with an experimental base for planting high-quality poplars.
</P>
<P>
Jinshatan Prefecture, located in the north of the province, has
planted more than 730 types of poplars from home and 270 from
abroad. According to the different natural conditions, areas such
as northeast China's Heilongjiang Province and central China's
Hunan Province planted fine varieties of poplars which were
introduced from the prefecture.
</P>
<P>
In addition, Shanxi has sent 14 investigation groups and 35
technical personnel to Germany in recent years with the aim of
promoting local forestry technologies, according to the local
sources. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
