<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Greek Prime Minister Rounds up Visit to Czech Republic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Greece is backing the Czech
Republic's bid to join NATO and the European Union, Greek Prime
Minister Costantinos Simitis said here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Greece has also offered to share its experience with the Czech
government in its application bids, he said after meeting with
Czech President Vaclav Havel.
</P>
<P>
Simitis, who rounded up his three-day official visit on
Wednesday afternoon, was the first Greek head of state to visit
the Czech Republic since its independence.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, Simitis also met Czech Prime Minister Josef
Tosovsky, Chamber of Deputies Chairman Milos Zeman and Senate
Chairman Petr Pithart.
</P>
<P>
Both sides agreed to enhance political, economic, technological
and cultural cooperation between the two countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
