<HEADLINE> Iran Loses First Warm-up in France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 17 (Xinhua) -- World Cup qualifier Iran suffered a
1-0 defeat against French first division team Guingamp in its
first game of the three-match French tour on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
This was the first match for Iran on the French soil in 22
years, and was surely resulted from the tuneup for the World Cup
finals in France this summer.
</P>
<P>
At Guingamp, Iran displayed some good touches but eventually
lost to an 82nd minute volley by Laurent Herve.
</P>
<P>
"We were unable to maintain attacks and need to work on our
organization," said coach Tonislav Ivic after the match.
</P>
<P>
Iran will play Nantes on Friday and Montpellier on Monday to
conclude its tour. 
</P>
</TEXT>
