<HEADLINE> Brazil Names Players For Clash against Germany </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Romario and Bebeto were
summoned on Tuesday to complete the Brazilian team for a World Cup
warmup against Germany next week.
</P>
<P>
The Brazilian squad is to be composed of 10 players from local
clubs and 12 in foreign teams who were named last week. Most of
them are sure names at the World Cup this summer.
</P>
<P>
On March 25, the Brazilians will fly to Stuttgart to face
Germany for a true test of their capability to retain the World
Cup title under coach Mario Zagallo.
</P>
<P>
Romario and Bebeto were the pair who led Brazil to its fourth
World Cup title in 1994.
</P>
<P>
Besides them, the Brazilian roster includes goalie Taffarel and
midfielder Denilson, both considered starters on the Cup team.
</P>
<P>
Defenders Junior Baiano, Goncalves and Ze Roberto are also sure
to make the final cut.
</P>
<P>
However, there also were some surprises. Goalie Dida got the
nod over Carlos Germano, repeatedly called by Zagallo as the No. 2
goalie. Fullback Cleber of Palmeiras also got a chance.
</P>
<P>
The big surprise was lateral Ze Carlos of Sao Paulo, who will
make his debut on the national team. That may be a sign that
Zagallo wasn't happy with the much-criticized play of Ze Maria in
the Gold Cup.
</P>
<P>
Following are the namelist for the friendly:
</P>
<P>
Goalies: Taffarel (Atletico Mineiro) and Dida (Cruzeiro)
</P>
<P>
Defenders: Roberto Carlos (Real Madrid), Cafu (Roma), Aldair
(Roma), Ze Carlos (Sao Paulo), Junior Baiano (Flamengo), Goncalves
(Botafogo) and Ze Roberto (Flamengo)
</P>
<P>
Midfielders: Leonardo (Milan), Rai (Paris Saint-Germain),
Doriva (Porto), Ze Elias (Internazionale), Dunga (Jubilo Iwata),
Cesar Sampaio (Yokohama Flugels), Rivaldo (Barcelona) and Denilson
(Sao Paulo)
</P>
<P>
Forwards: Ronaldo (Internazionale), Elber (Bayern Munich),
Romario (Flamengo) and Bebeto (Botafogo). 
</P>
</TEXT>
