<HEADLINE> Atletico Advances into UEFA Cup Last Four </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 17 (XInhua) -- Atletico Madrid of Spain squeezed
into the semifinals of the UEFA Cup despite their 2-1 second-leg
loss to Aston Villa in Brimingham, Britain, on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The two sides tied 2-2 on aggregate in the quarterfinals but
the Spanish club won on the away goals rule following their 1-0
triumph in Madrid two weeks ago.
</P>
<P>
Atletico opened the scoring the 29th minute through Jose Luis
Caminero.
</P>
<P>
Villa rallied to net twice within three minutes, one from Ian
Taylor in the 71st and the other from substitute Stan Collymore in
the 73rd. 
</P>
</TEXT>
