<HEADLINE> Forest Tourism Booming in East China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, March 18 (Xinhua) -- East China's Anhui Province has
become a major tourist attraction in the country because of its
wider forest coverage.
</P>
<P>
Mountainous areas in the province provide more than 266,000
hectares, 73 percent of which are covered with trees.
</P>
<P>
The province leads the country in terms of the number of forest
parks. It now has 23 state-level and 12 province-level forest
parks totaling nearly 114,000 hectares.
</P>
<P>
The forest parks attract 4 million domestic and overseas
tourists per year.
</P>
<P>
During recent years, the province has raised millions of yuan
through different channels for the planning and construction of
local forest parks.
</P>
<P>
More than 20 local forest parks, including those at Huangshan
and Juihuashan mountains, have been opened to overseas visitors
and are expected to earn more than 100 million yuan a year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
