<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, March 17 (Xinhua) -- U.S. stocks closed higher on
Tuesday with the Dow Jones industrial average up 31.14 points to
8,749.99 following Monday's staggering advance of 116 points.
</P>
<P>
The 30 blue chip company index recovered from an early loss of
35 points caused by profit-taking and market sentiment on the
disappointing first quarter earning estimates of some technology
companies.
</P>
<P>
With today's gain, the Dow earned an accumulated 841.74 points
this year, or a 10.64 percent expansion.
</P>
<P>
On the New York Stock Exchange, advancing issues was led by
decliners with 1,472 up, 1,511 down and 526 unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Trading volume amounted to 674.02 million shares against 546.83
million shares yesterday.
</P>
<P>
Broader market indicators ended mixed with the Standard &AMP;
Poor's 500 stock list up 1.18 to 1,080.45 and the NYSE composite
index up 1.15 to 563.09. The technology heavy Nasdaq composite
index fell 8.88 to 1,779.30.
</P>
<P>
The Russell 2000 index of smaller companies fell 0.66 to 471.10
while the small company dominated American Stock Exchange
composite index inched up 0.02 to 718.16. 
